      "weather": "",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUST A FAVOUR (1) proved too good on debut over 300m at Taree Super Track to score by 8 lengths (17.53). Drawn to take advantage of good early pace. Will break from the same draw this time. Can continue the winning form. NATALIE KEEPING (8) hit the ground running off the tricky draw and gave a sight in front, boxing on well for a minor when second (22.07) at this track in a Novice race over 381m. Likely to be in the finish again. ELITE ARNOTT (2) scored a 0.8 lengths win this course and distance last time in a personal Best Time (21.89) and also clocked one of the quickest wins on the card. Harder here but will be in this for a long way. RIPPIN' DUBLIN (4) was strongly fancied on the back of a win two starts back but finished third last time (22.26) at this track. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from three attempts.",
